creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Sea Poems: An Idiosyncratic Selection by Various.
Read in English by David Wales

Seventeen poems about the sea or in which the sea plays an important role. - Summary by david wales

The selection includes: The Rime Of The Ancient Mariner, by Samuel Taylor Coleridge
The Kraken, by Alfred Tennyson
Dover Beach, by Matthew Arnold
Ariel's Song in The Tempest (Act 1, Scene 2), by William Shakespeare
A Sea Dirge, by Lewis Carroll
The Jumblies, by Edward Lear
Dutch Lullaby (Wynken Blynken And Nod), by Eugene Field
Down To The Sea In Ships, Psalm 107:21-31, in The Bible, KJV
O Captain, My Captain, by Walt Whitman
The New Colossus, by Emma Lazarus
By The Sea, by Emily Dickinson
The Admiral's Ghost, by Alfred Noyes
A Lover's Quarrel, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox
A Channel Passage, by Rupert Brooke
On The Seas And Far Away, by Robert Burns
North Atlantic, by Carl Sandburg
Crossing The Bar, by Alfred Tennyson

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
